Write a Row-Level Formula
Writing a row-level formula adds a row-level formula column to your report that makes calculations on every report row. 
Available in: Lightning Experience, Essentials, Group, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions
To create, edit, and delete formulas in private reports: Enhanced Folder Sharing
To create, edit, and delete formulas in public and private reports: Enhanced Folder Sharing

Create or edit a report.
From the Columns section of the Outline pane, click Add Row-Level Formula.
From the Edit Row-Level Formula Column window, enter a Column Name, choose a Formula Output Type, and write a Formula. Optionally, enter a Description and set the number of Decimal Points.

To test your formula for errors, click Validate. If necessary, resolve any errors. Then, click Apply.

The row-level formula appears as a column on the report.
To save and run the report, click Save & Run.
